Reasoning: The paper presents a deterministic polynomial time algorithm for testing invertibility of symbolic matrices in non-commuting variables over $\mathbb{Q}$, which is a problem in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The algorithm also solves the word problem for the free skew field and the identity testing problem for arithmetic formulae with division over non-commuting variables, which are problems in data structures (cs.DS) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions applications in quantum information theory (cs.QA) and information theory (cs.IT).
